The purpose of this task is to structure information needed to search for restaurants by extracting relevant criteria, including:
- Rating: subjective or objective indicators of quality or user preference, e.g., "good", "best", "highly rated".
- Amenity: special features or facilities provided by the restaurant, e.g., "great view", "outdoor seating".
- Location: any mention of geographic area, neighborhood, or distance, e.g., "downtown", "within 5 miles".
- Restaurant_Name: the exact name of a restaurant as mentioned in the query.
- Price: any explicit mention of cost or price range, e.g., "cheap", "expensive", "affordable".
- Hours: references to timing or open hours, e.g., "open late", "24 hours".
- Dish: specific food items or dishes, e.g., "poek", "sushi".
- Cuisine: type or style of food served, e.g., "italian", "mexican".

Each value must be a substring of the input query text—never rewrite or standardize slot values. If a word or phrase could belong to more than one slot type, assign it to all relevant types. Pay attention to context to avoid grouping unrelated words in a single slot—for example, "great" as a Rating is distinct from "great view" as an Amenity, and "great poek" should not be treated as a single Dish unless that phrase appears explicitly in the query.

Your output must be only the JSON object, structured as described. Do not include any other explanatory text.
