For each slot type, find and extract all matching spans that appear as exact substrings in the query. Use only the literal text from the query as the value for each slot.

Requirements:
- Only return a JSON object, mapping each slot type (as keys) to a list of the exact substrings (from the query text) that represent its values.
- Only include slot types that actually appear in the user query.
- For multiple or repeated entities, include each as a separate entry in the list for that slot type.
- Never paraphrase or canonicalize text; only output exact substrings as they appear.
- If there are no entities of a given slot type in the query, do not include that type in the output.

Slot type guidelines:
- "Restaurant_Name": Proper names of restaurants, as written in the query, e.g. "buca de beppo", "jon morris and companys".
- "Cuisine": Words or phrases indicating cuisine types, e.g. "italian", "mexican".
- "Location": Phrases or words that describe a location or proximity, eg. "nearest", "along the way", or named places.
- "Amenity": Services or features offered by the restaurant, e.g. "carry out", "delivery", "wifi".
- "Rating": Any mention of review ratings or values, e.g. "4 stars", "highly rated".
- "Price": Any mention of price level or cost, e.g. "cheap", "expensive".
- "Hours": Any mention of time or schedule for operation or availability, e.g. "open now", "24 hours".
- "Dish": Any specific foods or menu items mentioned, e.g. "pizza", "pasta".

Return ONLY the JSON object as specified, and do not include any text or explanation outside the valid JSON.
