- "Rating" includes terms or phrases referring to quality, ranking, or user reviews (examples: "best", "best rated").
- "Amenity" refers to specific features or services a restaurant offers (examples: "drive thru", "outdoor seating").
- "Location" relates to geographical or positional information (examples: "near me", "in austin").
- "Restaurant_Name" refers to the name of a specific restaurant chain or store (examples: "subway", "starbucks").
- "Price" includes any terms reflecting cost or expense level (examples: "cheap", "affordable").
- "Hours" includes opening or closing times, or references to time windows (examples: "open now", "24 hours").
- "Dish" refers to specific food items or meals (examples: "bbq ribs", "pasta").
- "Cuisine" refers to the style or tradition of food served (examples: "bbq", "italian").

Omit any slot types that do not occur in the input query. The output must be restricted ONLY to the JSON object mapping present slot types to their corresponding substrings from the query. Do not include any additional text or explanation.

Examples:
- Input: "where is the best bbq in austin"
